messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 8/19/2004 10:47:10 PM Eastern Daylight Time,
UnschoolingDiscussion@yahoogroups.com writes:
If you get the HBO stable of channels, keep a look out for a documentary
titled "Jackie Chan: My Stunts" in which he talks about, well, his stunts.
I think I may have seen that, one of those months we had free so&so channel.
He explained how thay set up and practice all the stunts in his gym. One thing
I remember is the amount of fun and laughter between the crew.
I think Jackie Chan needs to be on my "Who would you invite to dinner" list.
"Excuse me Mr. Chan, would you please pass the peas?"

Elissa Jill

Life's challenges are not supposed to paralyze you;
They're supposed to help you discover who you are.
~Bernice Johnson Reagon
